{% extends "case.njk" %}
{% set title = "Your Activity for Babbel" %}
{% set slug = "babbel-activity" %}
{% set description = "Simple learning activity tracker for Babbel" %}
{% block colors %}
<style type='text/css'>
    :root {
        --bg: #f2f2f2;
        --fg: #0c2e44;
    }
</style>
{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<p>
    In Autumn 2018 while working at <a href='https://babbel.com'>Babbel</a> I was presented with a
    peculiar problem that long haunted our learners: loss of motivation. Language learning is a
    complex task that takes lots of effort and time. To be successful a learner needs to practice
    often. The sense of progression is minimal: language proficiency is one of the most complex
    skills to learn. It's not enough to grasp the basics and figure out the rules, one needs to
    practice those skills until using them doesn't require thinking on conscious level.
</p>
<figure class='full'>
    <img
        srcset='
            images/highlighted-400.webp 400w,
            images/highlighted-600.webp 600w,
            images/highlighted-800.webp 800w,
            images/highlighted-1000.webp 1000w,
            images/highlighted-1200.webp 1200w,
            images/highlighted-2048.webp 2048w
        '
        sizes='
            (min-width: 1024px) 1024px,
            100vw
        '
        src='images/highlighted-400.webp'
        alt='Feature in context on desktop home screen'
        width='512'
        height='443'
        class='clamped'
        style='--width: 1024px'
        loading='eager'
    >
    <figcaption>Feature in context on desktop home screen</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>
    The flow that we wanted to achieve from implementing our feature was a simple repetitive pattern
    of practice. A little help for those learners who feel overwhelmed and start to fall behind on
    their studies.
</p>
<figure class='full'>
    <img
        srcset='
            images/flow-400.webp 400w,
            images/flow-600.webp 600w,
            images/flow-800.webp 800w,
            images/flow-1000.webp 1000w,
            images/flow-1200.webp 1200w,
            images/flow-2187.webp 2187w
        '
        sizes='100vw'
        src='images/flow-400.webp'
        alt='User flow diagram'
        width='2187'
        height='751'
        loading='lazy'
    >
    <figcaption>User flow</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>
    We ran a cross-disciplinary (project management, development, instructional design, product
    marketing, product design) workshop to figure out the minimum viable solution that will achieve
    this goal. We used card sorting to figure out the steps of existing flow and point of impact
    where we can slightly adjust things to have more positive reinforcement.
</p>
<figure class='full'>
    <img
        srcset='
            images/cardsorting-400.webp 400w,
            images/cardsorting-600.webp 600w,
            images/cardsorting-800.webp 800w,
            images/cardsorting-1000.webp 1000w,
            images/cardsorting-1200.webp 1200w,
            images/cardsorting-2000.webp 2000w,
            images/cardsorting-4032.webp 4032w
        '
        sizes='100vw'
        src='images/cardsorting-400.webp'
        alt='Post-its on the wall'
        width='252'
        height='189'
        loading='lazy'
    >
    <figcaption>Photo of card sorting excercise</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>
    Based on this exercise we used a whiteboard to map a more detailed user flow. We noted existing
    solutions, features that were being worked on in parallel and points of impact where we wanted
    to add something.
</p>
<figure class='full'>
    <img
        srcset='
            images/mapping-400.webp 400w,
            images/mapping-600.webp 600w,
            images/mapping-800.webp 800w,
            images/mapping-1000.webp 1000w,
            images/mapping-1200.webp 1200w,
            images/mapping-2000.webp 2000w,
            images/mapping-4032.webp 4032w
        '
        sizes='100vw'
        src='images/mapping-400.webp'
        alt='Drawing of flowchart on whiteboard'
        width='252'
        height='189'
        loading='lazy'
    >
    <figcaption>Detailed user flow</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>
    I sketched more detailed interface compositions for points of impact; got some quick feedback on
    what would be the easiest to implement but still meaningful for learners from participants of
    the work group who participated in the workshop.
</p>
<figure class='full'>
    <img
        srcset='
            images/sketches-400.webp 400w,
            images/sketches-600.webp 600w,
            images/sketches-800.webp 800w,
            images/sketches-1000.webp 1000w,
            images/sketches-1557.webp 1557w
        '
